2.41	Shtora	Shtora	Shtora (Russian: , "curtain") is an electro-optical active protection system or suite for tanks, designed to disrupt the laser target designation and rangefinders of incoming anti-tank guided missiles (ATGMs). The system is mounted on the Russian T-80 and T-90 series tanks, the Ukrainian T-84 and the Serbian M-84AS.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/VDayParade2009.jpg/300px-VDayParade2009.jpg
